To model the luminance-distance experimental data, we consider the OLED as three layers (Fig. 4b): a MoO3–x layer (bottom electrode), an emitting layer (top EL), and a top Al cathode. The thicknesses of these layers and the dimensions of the y coordinate are much smaller than the lateral dimensions of the x coordinate of the OLED device. In the model we can make the following approximations:
The cathode can be considered as a perfect conductor and it is grounded, φt = 0;
The potential in the MoO3–x layer is practically independent of the y coordinate and z coordinate, φb(x);
The current density in the emitting layer is perpendicular to the substrate, jz
